You are running the red-herring puzzle E2E test. This test exercises the polling diff recorder (`__scummRecordStart`, `__scummRecordSummary`). The game is Monkey Island 1 demo, you are in room 55.

Background: the puzzle requires pushing a hidden object (id 307) to scare the bird (actor id 7) away from the red herring (object id 306). Only then can you pick up the herring. The bird moves for a few seconds; you must grab the herring while it is far enough away.

Step 1 — Navigate to the dock area. The route is:
  Room 55  →  (door object 422, need to Open first if closed, then Walk to) →  Room 52 (Scumm Bar)
  Room 52  →  (door object 354, Open + Walk to, then `__scummWalkTo(315, 130)` inside)  →  Room 51 (kitchen)
  Room 51  →  (door object 304, Open + Walk to, then `__scummWalkTo(250, 129)`)  →  Room 51 outside (dock)

Use `__scummDoSentence({verb: 1, objectA: <doorId>})` (Open) then `__scummDoSentence({verb: 10, objectA: <doorId>})` (Walk to). After each step, poll `__scummRead().room` with a hard timeout (`Date.now() - start > 20000`) to confirm the transition — and inspect `roomObjects` in the new room to find the next door's id (the 422/354/304 ids come from the briefing / analysis but may drift — confirm from `__scummRead()` each time).

When you see object id 306 ("red herring") in `roomObjects`, you are in the dock area.

Step 2 — Baseline: try to pick up the red herring BEFORE pushing the bird. The bird blocks — this should produce a message like "I think that bird will peck my hand off."
```js
(() => {
  const s = __scummRead();
  window.__e2eTestResults.inventoryBefore = s.inventory.map(i => i.name);
  window.__e2eTestResults.grabBeforePushResult = __scummDoSentence({verb: 11, objectA: 306});
  return window.__e2eTestResults.grabBeforePushResult;
})()
```
Wait ~4s for any cutscene / message to resolve, then `__scummSkipMessage()` if needed.

Step 3 — Start the recorder, push 307, then grab the herring while the bird is away.
```js
__scummRecordClear && __scummRecordClear();
__scummRecordStart({intervalMs: 100});
```
Now push the hidden trigger: `__scummDoSentence({verb: 6, objectA: 307})` (Push). Then, in a SINGLE bounded eval, poll the bird's position until it has moved far away OR timeout, then grab the herring. Hard-bracket the loop.
```js
(async () => {
  const start = Date.now();
  while (Date.now() - start < 15000) {
    const s = __scummRead();
    if (s && s.inputLocked === false) {
      const bird = (s.actors || []).find(a => a.id === 7);
      if (bird && bird.pos && bird.pos.x > 265) {
        const r = __scummDoSentence({verb: 11, objectA: 306});
        return { grabbed: true, at: bird.pos, result: r };
      }
    }
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 100));
  }
  return { grabbed: false };
})()
```

Step 4 — Wait for the pick-up animation / any message to complete (sleep 3-4s then skipMessage if haveMsg). Stop the recorder and capture the summary + inventory:
```js
(() => {
  const summary = __scummRecordSummary();
  __scummRecordStop();
  const s = __scummRead();
  const r = window.__e2eTestResults;
  r.summaryAfterPush = summary;
  r.recorderFilteredAnimationPaths = summary.filteredAnimationPaths;
  r.inventoryAfter = s.inventory.map(i => i.name);
  // Extract seenValues for bird pos.x if present
  const birdX = (summary.changes || []).find(c =>
    Array.isArray(c.path) && c.path[0] === 'actors' && c.path[3] === 'x' &&
    typeof c.path[1] === 'object' && c.path[1].id === 7);
  r.birdSeenValues = birdX && birdX.seenValues || null;
  // Extract msgText seenValues if present
  const msg = (summary.changes || []).find(c =>
    Array.isArray(c.path) && c.path.length === 1 && c.path[0] === 'msgText');
  r.msgTextSeenValues = msg && msg.seenValues || null;
  return r;
})()
```

Step 5 — If you did not manage to grab the herring within the timeout, document that in your final message and stop — the runner will fail the inventory assertion.

Rules:
- Never write an unbounded polling loop.
- Check `inputLocked` before every action; wait for cutscenes to end.
- If a door does not open or a walk does not transition the room, retry ONCE then move on.
- After each action, wait 1-3 seconds before reading state.
